column1: Kike Coronado knows that Congressman Henry Cuellar fights for all South Texans. By bringing better paying jobs to his district Rep. Cuellar puts working families first. https://t.co/RReh1dxGB5
My prayers go out to the President and the First Lady as well as every American battling the coronavirus.  https://t.co/gGIy2BnRXn

Atascosa Health Center serves six counties including Atascosa McMullen and Wilson. These funds will improve efficiency in their delivery and quality of care especially as we continue to address COVID-19.

COVID-19 has devastated our communities along the southern border and we must find a way to minimize public health risks while still allowing for our small businesses to resume economic operations. https://t.co/SrtYTDKfoT

In honor of the #2020DemConvention I found myself reminiscing about the one in 2016. Although COVID19 has restructured this year’s event the message remains the same. To create a more perfect union we must work to serve all Americans ensuring that every voice is heard. https://t.co/TSqacQcD86

ICYMI: You have until midnight on August 9 to take advantage of the tax-free weekend. While in the Texas State Legislature I helped create this Sales Tax Holiday as a way to assist families in preparing for the new school year. Don’t forget to social distance & wear a mask. https://t.co/YTlLmJ4o3N

South Texas families are struggling to make ends meet during the COVID-19 pandemic and many are having to choose between food and other necessities. Organizations like the Laredo Regional Food Bank are working overtime to supply households with food to put on their tables.

This is unacceptable. We must continue to prioritize the safety and well-being of Texans across the state. My thoughts and prayers are with those who are battling COVID-19 as well as those who’ve lost a loved one due to this virus. https://t.co/dOsFbnP5Rs

Lives are at stake - families are facing eviction children are facing food insecurities and small businesses are struggling.  COVID-19 knows no boundaries and has impacted nearly every community one way or another.
Protect yourself and those around you by wearing a face mask and washing your hands constantly. Together we can make a difference in reducing the spread of #COVID19 https://t.co/EnC3qEO6Lo

As we face the impact of COVID-19 we must ensure that those who have served our country with their lives are kept in the workforce. I will continue working to ensure veterans in the 28th District of Texas and throughout our nation are taken care of. #HireAVeteran #USveterans https://t.co/4ipQdrHIID

During this time it’s crucial that we stay strong and continue the fight against the spread of COVID-19 as a community. As we see cases surging throughout South Texas  let’s pray for those who are sick and those who have lost the battle. https://t.co/nydJ6dDko5

🇺🇸 Happy Independence Day! 🇺🇸  I encourage you to continue practicing social distance using face coverings and washing your hands constantly. Keep yourself and those around you safe.   #happy4thofjuly #independenceday https://t.co/VbKU7NrFpR

Texas is seeing a spike in #COVID19 cases and hospitalizations. We must continue to do our part and wear face coverings or masks when out in public. Not only will we protect ourselves but we’ll also protect those around us. https://t.co/AY5a4BXxzw

COVID-19 is still affecting our communities. Make sure to continue practicing social distancing clean hygiene & wearing face coverings when out in public. @TexasHHSC has a #COVID19 Self-Checker to help you determine if you need testing. Find out here 🔽  https://t.co/LGXDPVYcZp

Our farmers & ranchers in rural areas are struggling during the COVID19 outbreak. As someone who serves on the Subcommittee on Agriculture I’ll continue to fight for rural counties across my district & ensure that these hard working individuals are receiving the help they need.

With the constant flow of information being released in regard to #COVID19 it can be difficult to distinguish what’s true and what’s not. @FEMA has published a ‘Coronavirus Rumor Control’ to help you stay up to date with their response to this pandemic:  https://t.co/TOhtlst71z

As the SBA continues to address #COVID19 they’ve begun hiring temporary employees to assist with disaster relief efforts. Remote jobs are available and bilingual language skills are a plus.   For more info: https://t.co/8CYoZckfo2

If you have symptoms of #COVID19 and want to get tested call your doctor first. Also check with your state or local health department which will have the latest information on testing. Learn more: https://t.co/OclW4LgKVS

Today I voted for the interim coronavirus relief package to ensure that we protect hard working Americans and keep our communities safe and healthy.

While many of us are #StayingHome to slow the spread of coronavirus it’s also important we use this time to take care of our mental/physical health. These tips and resources can help boost your mood reduce stress sharpen your focus and improve sleep. https://t.co/WM872RA8Ce

Thank you to all the selfless volunteers who are helping our communities overcome challenges as a result of #COVID19. You’re acts of kindness and sincerity are a source of light during these dark times. https://t.co/AShrwceihb

Small businesses are the backbone to our economy and right now they need our help more than ever. Unfortunately COVID-19 has left many of these businesses struggling. When I voted to pass the CARES Act I voted for working families across our district
